howAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14851.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dropping all hell levels except 54 &amp; 59 ?</span><hr size=1> In regards to how level 60's will feel about this, since I was one of the level 60's errm 58's that had some mild disappointment about the Rez thing, (erm I think Im going to be defending myself over this forever), I really dont think we will care. <br><br>After leveling through all of the hell levels (some of them twice considering alts) the only ones that are really hell when compared to any level over 50 are 54 and 59. Since they are leaving those 2 levels as is according to the rumor we wont really care at all.<br><br>BTW some of the most productive things you can do in early level playing tend to be done during hell levels. Since the xp is going slowly anyway ppl tend to take a break and work on a trade skill or do a quest. They are also great times to increase weapon skills that may have been forgotten when you could make a level in an hour.  <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>58 Knight of Brell<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker</bold></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uskellt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skellt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 1:37:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14851.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dropping all hell levels except 54 &amp; 59 ?</span><hr size=1> I dislike Hell Levels myself, but I would like to point out that hell levels are actually beneficial to characters.  They do not slow you down at all.  The amount of xp needed to get from 31 to 35 was decided up front when they designed the game.  It isn't MORE because of hell levels, it's just distributed differently.  When they wrote the code, for whatever reason, it made 4 of the levels have less than a linear distribution, and 1 have more.  If you get 4 fast levels you are gaining skills, spells, hit points, increased resists, less greenie aggro, etc... fast.  This is much more beneficial than gaining 5 levels in an even distribution.  No hell levels would slow you down for 4 levels, but speed you up for 1.<br><br>For example if we take hell levels to the ultimate extreme, we might have all levels costing 1 xp, except for 59 which costs all the xp you should have earned in first 58.  While this would make level 59 REALLY SUCK, it is clear that people would gain levels faster and get more powerful more quickly.<br><br>They are certainly not going to make the extra xp in hell levels just vanish.  It will be disbributed amongst the 4 prior levels making them slower to gain. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucaebesilverfish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caebe Silverfish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 755<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 1:43:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14851.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dropping all hell levels except 54 &amp; 59 ?</span><hr size=1> i seem to remember something or another about &quot;We (verant) has decided it will take &quot;X&quot; amount of XP for &quot;Y&quot; level, and if hell levels were removed, then that XP would just be linearly distributed over the entire level&quot;<br><br>anybody else remember something to that gist?<br> <p><html><p align="center"><font color="#FFFF