ty Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: dropping all hell levels except 54 &amp; 59 ?</span><hr size=1> The only really bad HELL level is 59, where the level modifier jumps 3 points.<br><br>Below that, levels 58, 57, 56, 55, 54 ALL have level modifier jumps of 2 points. There is nothing special about level 54 its all 5 of those levels. Still a common misconception after all this time.<br><br>Below those are levels, 53, 52, 51, 45, 40, 35, 30, which all have a modifier jump of 1 point.<br><br>All other levels do not have a modifer change.<br><br>Really simple to remove them if they want, as others have said just need to add a modifier to the exp you recieve during hell levels. <br><br>The modifier would be (total_exp_to_fill_current_level - total_exp_to_fill_last_level)/(total_exp_to_fill_current_level - total_exp_to_fill_last_level*currentlevelmod/lastlevemod)<br><br>And hell levels vanish, but they keep getting harder then just level^3, ie the level modifier they have still means something.<br><br>However i dont believe they should do this. Granted levels 51-60 take a long time....but a players increase in power during those levels is HUGE. If they wanna remove hell levels they should do 30/35/40/35, and leave in levels 51-59, they could make them a little easier then they are now if they want, but i definately do not think they should be made much easier.<br><br>Levels 51-59 take no where near as long these days as they did when kunark first came out. With all the new weapons/armor can get exp much faster. Weapons considered trash these days are better then the best people had when kunark came out. Each expansion they add, leveling only becomes easier. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=14851.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><b